questionTemplates.text:
W: I haven't studied much English this week at all.
M: Why worry? We have a vacation coming up. Soon you'll have lots of time.
{a}

W: How do you feel today?
M: I still have a headache, but my temperature has gone down.
{a}

M: Do you know where Lily is?
W: She was here. Hm... Try then next room.
{a}

M: Mary, would you like to have a picnic with us tomorrow?
W: Sorry, but mum asked me to go shopping with her.
{a}

F: Did you enjoy yourselves at the party last night?
M: Oh, our car broke down on the way, and we didn't get there.
{a}

F: Can you see any birds in the tree?
M: Hardly any.
{a}

M: Daisy was furious yesterday because I lost her notebook. Should I go see her and apologize to her again?
W: Well, if I were you, I'd let her cool off a few days before I approach her.
{a}

M: I can't find the key to my car, I need to go for a drive.
W: I'll look for it later. Right now I want you to help fix the shelf before I paint it.
{a}

M: How long can I keep them?
W: Ten days. Then you will have to return them; otherwise you will be fined for being overdue.
{a}

M: Can you lend me five dollars?
W: I had ten dollars but I just spent seven.
{a}

W: What are you going to have?
M: I'm going to order scrambled eggs and toast.
{a}

F: Excuse me, can you tell me what do you want to be after you graduate?
M: I want to be an engineer.
{a}

F: Come on, John. The play starts at seven thirty.
M: Well, don't worry. We have twenty minutes to get there.
{a}

W: Can I borrow your dictionary?
M: Sorry, I left it home this morning.
{a}

M: Thank you very much for the meal.
F: Not at all. I'm glad you could come.
{a}

W: John, do you want to go swimming with me today?
M: Sure, but I can't leave now. I have an appointment with my professor at 3o'clock.
{a}

M: You call Henry a dreamer, but I think he's got a lot of good ideas.
W: Good ideas are only useful if you make something out of them.
{a}

M: Congratulations, Li Ming. You are the talk of the town, and the pride of our class now.
W: If you are referring to my winning the English Speech Contest, I don't think it's such a big deal. You know I've spent two summer vacations learning English in Canada.
{a}

W: I can't understand my notes from Spanish class.
M: How about reviewing them now over a cup of tea?
{a}

Man: I heard on the radio that it'll be sunny during the holiday weekend. Maybe we can take a trip to Boston.
Woman: That sounds great. I'll call Jean to see if she likes to join us.
{a}

W: The play was wonderful.
M: Do you really think so?
{a}

W: I'm going to the supermarket. What would you like me to buy for you?
M: Will you please buy some fruit for me while you're there?
{a}

M: If you are looking for the Time, I think I've got the last copy.
W: Oh, Well, I think I will get some newspaper to read instead.
{a}
